context: In the <a2_0><b6_0>UK, Italy and Australia<b6_0/><a2_0/> which share the PAL A region, two versions of the NES were released; the <a3_0>"<b4_0><b7_0>Mattel<b4_0/> Version<b7_0/>" and "NES Version"<a3_0/>. When the NES was first released in those countries, it was distributed by <a0_0>Mattel<a0_0/> and Nintendo decided to use a lockout chip specific to those countries, different from the chip used in other European countries. When Nintendo took over European distribution in <a1_0><b5_0>1990<b5_0/><a1_0/>, they produced consoles that were then labelled "NES Version"; therefore, the only differences between the two are the text on the front flap and texture on the top/bottom of the casing.
